Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Systems Analyst Victoria , BC Description Library Systems Analyst Competition: LA242531 Department: Legislative Library Position Type: Auxiliary Full-Time (until January 2026) Salary Range: $72,892.23 - $91,115.29 per annum + 8% vacation pay Close Date: Wednesday, October 2, 2024 at 12:00pm (noon) PDT POSITION SUMMARY Employees of the Legislative Assembly of British Columbia (Assembly) provide professional non-partisan services to support the democratic institution of Parliament and its members through procedural advice, administrative support and information services. The Assembly is an autonomous employer, separate from the administrative framework of B.C. government ministries and agencies. The Legislative Library is seeking a detail-oriented and customer-focused individual for the auxiliary full-time position of Library Systems Analyst. Reporting to the Systems and Technical Services Manager, the Library Systems Analyst, working as part of the Library Systems team, is responsible for developing, implementing, maintaining, and troubleshooting software and hardware for library clients and staff. This role involves creating and improving code for managing library collections and services, technical support for library services and applications, and writing and maintaining documentation and training materials. The analyst ensures the smooth operation of library systems and supports the technological needs of both staff and patrons. QUALIFICATIONS Applicants must be/have: Post-secondary education in a technology related field such as information technology or computer sciences, plus at least 3 years of relevant experience* within an IT environment, or an equivalent combination of education and experience. *Relevant experience may include:Maintaining client/server and web application architecture. Developing software applications.Providing technical support. Preference may be given to candidates with the following:Experience working in a Library systems environment. Please refer to the job description for a full list of duties and qualifications. APPLICATION REQUIREMENTS Please submit cover letter and résumé through our job board portal ( https://www.leg.bc.ca/about/careers/job-postings ) by 12:00pm (noon) PDT on Wednesday, October 2, 2024. For questions please email human.resources@leg.bc.ca. Compensation $72,892.23 - $91,115.29 per annum + 8% vacation pay Closes: 2 October, 2024 Legislative Assembly of BC Victoria , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
