Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Community Outreach Specialist - Permanent Full-time King City , ON Description King Township Public Library (KTPL) serves a vibrant community of 27,000 residents through our multi-branch system. As part of the GTA, King residents are drawn to its rural lifestyle, village atmosphere and high quality of life. The staff and library system enjoy the strong support of the community. Position Summary: The Community Outreach Specialist will play an integral role in supporting the Library’s brand management, under the direction of the Manager of Engagement &amp; Connections. Primary duties will be to create the Library’s internal/external print and digital communications, to strengthen all marketing/communication campaigns, to assist with community relations and to represent the Library at community events held across the Township and Region. This position will also have a role in public service and support duties e.g. circulation and information services, which promote a welcoming and inviting library environment and meet the strategic direction set forth by the KTPL Board. While implementing special projects, on occasion, the Community Outreach Specialist may report to other senior managers. Qualifications: Post-secondary diploma in Library &amp; Information Technician program or related discipline2 years’ experience in a marketing/graphic design or a library environment Experience in graphic design using a variety of digital platforms, including image and video editing software Possesses a keen eye for design with the ability to incorporate creativity into their work Understands the basic principles of marketing and how they apply to library services or the non-profit/public sector Understands and uses popular social networking and online collaboration tools Familiarity with Integrated Library Systems (ILS) is considered an asset Critical thinking and analytical skills required to support the needs of the Library’s strategic goals Works as a team player, contributing to the overall success of the library and exhibits a learning and growth mindset Demonstrated proficiency in customer service Proof of valid Ontario Driver’s License, up-to-date insurance and reliable transportation is a must Able to work flexible hours, including evenings and weekends, at ALL branches within the library system Successful candidate will be required to produce a current Vulnerable Sector Check Fluent in English with excellent presentation, oral and written communication skills Minimum physical requirements: able to lift 30 pounds, bend, reach and stretch Hours of Work: 35 hours a week, including evenings and weekends Salary Range: Starting at $30.53/hour plus competitive benefit program Application Deadline: October 15, 2024 Interested applicants are invited to submit a cover letter and resume to: recruitment@kinglibrary.ca We thank all who apply but only those selected for an interview will be contacted. We are an Equal Opportunity Employer. In accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act, 2005 and the Ontario Human Rights Code, the King Township Public Library will provide accommodations throughout the recruitment, selection and/or assessment process to applicants with disabilities. If selected to participate in recruitment, selection and/or assessment process, please inform the library staff of the nature of any accommodation(s) that you may require in respect of any materials or processes used to ensure your equal participation. Compensation $29.34/hr Closes: 15 October, 2024 King Township Public Library King City , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
