Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Branch Head Librarian I - Lake Country Kelowna , BC Description Career Opportunity Branch Head Librarian I – Lake Country Okanagan Regional LibraryPermanent Full Time The Okanagan Regional Library (ORL) is seeking an experienced, passionate, visionary, and community-minded librarian to lead our branch in one of the fastest growing communities in BC, Lake Country. The Lake Country Branch Head Librarian I is a new addition to the staffing complement at the Lake Country branch and will be the first professional librarian at that location.Within the ORL system, Branch Heads are the key leadership position responsible for branch develop, branch operation and supervision of 10 employees. The Lake Country branch is a centrally located traditional library beloved by this rapidly growing community. All leadership librarians in ORL also work collectively to provide strategic direction and assist with project work in support of the entire library system. The successful candidate will bring with them proven experience in developing and maintaining partnerships using a community led libraries approach. The individual will be planning and organizing library branch resources and services to meet the community needs and interests.They will develop and maintain effective relationships with staff, be a team player with excellent interpersonal and communication skills, and stay current with trends, technologies, and best practices in public library services. Qualifications include: Master’s degree in, Library and Information Science from an accredited library school.Two years relevant public library experience. This position is permanent full-time 35 hours weekly. Salary range is $83,880 to $89,226 per year. Please visit our website at http://www.orl.bc.ca/careers/current-vacancies for the job description.Interested applicants should forward a covering letter, resume, and reference information via e-mail to: jobs@orl.bc.ca. We thank all applicants for their interest in our organization; however, only short-listed applicants will be contacted.Competition Number: 24-104 Compensation $83,880 to $89,226​ per year. Closes: 13 November, 2024 Okanagan Regional Library Kelowna , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
