Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Technician I - Collections Coquitlam , BC Description Position: Library Technician I - Collections Job Code: CPL2024-29 Position Type: Regular Full Time Hours of Work: 35 hours per week Location: All (Hours currently reside in PO) Department: E-Brach and Collections Pay Grade: Pay Grade 16 Hourly Rate: $30.85 per hour Posting Date: August 2, 2024 Closing Date: Until Filled Coquitlam Public Library Coquitlam Public Library creates joy in discovery, fosters inclusion and promotes knowledge by proving innovative experiences, spaces and services. We are committed to inclusion, team wellbeing &amp; culture, partnerships &amp; engagement, Truth &amp; Reconciliation and leading into the future, as well as increased library access through physical, online and mobile services. The library has two branches as well as the Library Link, our mobile library. Position Overview The Coquitlam Public Library is currently seeking a Library Technician I to join our team. The primary focus of this position will be to provide exceptional customer service to the patrons of the library and providing professional staff a variety of technical library support. Duties Include Performs derivative, descriptive and non-complex original or copy cataloguing of specified library materials and resources as directed and according to established standards, procedures and practicesPerforms non-complex work to increase the discoverability of the library collection, programs and services as directed, including the creation of booklists, displays and newsletters.Performs non-complex work related to the acquisition of library materials as directed, such as processing requisitions for library materials.Performs non-complex work related to the selection of items for collections as directed, such as creating selection lists based on specific criteria or subjects. Updates and maintains content on the library website and social mediaAssists with statistical documentation of the use of library collections, programs and services.Other duties as assigned. Conditions of Employment Successful incumbent must complete a criminal record check prior to commencing work; Required to join CUPE Local #561; Required to work at any branch in the Coquitlam Public Library system as well as Library Link. Requirements Completion of a Library Technician diploma.Sound knowledge of library methods, procedures and tools applicable to the work.Sound knowledge of the Dewey decimal classification system, the current international cataloguing rules, and the local cataloguing standards, procedures and practices as related to the work performed.Ability to assist the public in the access, location and use of a wide variety of internal and external source material, technical resources, and bibliographic tools. Strong command of English communication skills, including verbal and written a necessity. Well-developed interpersonal skills required as this position works with various library staff and the public. Ability to operate computer terminal and other library equipment. Strong keyboarding skills required. Travel between branches is required. Shifts may be assigned at any branch. What We Offer In addition to an excellent compensation package, we provide a working environment that supports knowledge, innovation and fun. With a strong focus on safety, we strive to inspire learning and service to our diverse community. If you have a proven commitment to providing exceptional customer service in a team environment, with a friendly, patient and outgoing personality, we are interested in hearing from you. TO APPLY FOR THIS POSITION: Please send an email to humanresources@coqlibrary.cawith your cover letter and resume attached in PDF format. The subject line must include the job code. If you are applying for more than one posting, only one email is required; however, please include all applicable job codes in the subject line. Only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation 30.85 per hour Closes: 4 November, 2024 Coquitlam Public Library Coquitlam , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
